cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD

This paper analyzes Altmetric.com, which is a tool used to measure the impact of research publications through social media and other online sources. Based on this description, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper deals with the collection and analysis of data related to research publications. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Development and Programming Languages), as these areas also involve the study of online data and its impact on society and research.
